<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880726-0020 </DOCNO><HL> Credit Ratings </HL><SO> </SO><CO> MEL </CO><IN> BON STK FIN </IN><DATELINE> MELLON BANK Corp.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Standard andamp; Poor's Corp. said it placed about $388 million of this Pittsburgh-based concern's debt on CreditWatch with positive implications. The ratings agency said the affected issues are Mellon's triple-B-plus senior debt; triple-B subordinated debt and triple-B-minus preferred stock; Mellon Financial Co.'s triple-B-plus senior debt and Mellon Bank and Mellon Bank (East)'s single-A-minus/ A-2 certificates of deposit and issues supported by letters of credit. Sandamp;P's action follows Mellon's announcement yesterday that it plans to shed about $1 billion in problem loans and sell $525 million in common and preferred stock. Mellon declined comment. </TEXT></DOC>